author: Rockland/Westchester Journal News, Joseph Spector, Rockland/Westchester Journal News
title: New data on New York coronavirus deaths: Most had these underlying illnesses; 61% were men
description: The majority of New York's more than 4,700 coronavirus deaths were among men, and 86% of all deaths were among people who had underlying illnesses.
content:
President Donald Trump said there's "light at the end of the tunnel" as his administration continues to fight the coronavirus outbreak.
